definition.value: An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-O-sulfo-alpha-L-idopyranuronic acid and 2-acetamido-D-galatopyranose residues joined by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
An amino disaccharide that is 2-acetamido-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy group at position 6 has been glycosylated by an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl group.
A glycosylglucopyranuronic acid consisting of beta-D-xylosyl and beta-D-glucuronic acid residues joined by a (1->3) glycosidic linkage.

A branched amino heptasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by an alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group.

An aminotetrasaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-beta-D-glucopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose, 2-acetamido-beta-D-glucopyranose and 2-acetamido-D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->3) glycosidic linkages.
An amino disaccharide consisting of two molecules of 2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose linked by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A disaccharide derivative consisting of alpha-L-threo-hex-4-enopyranuronic acid and 2-deoxy-6-O-sulfo-2-(sulfoamino)-alpha-D-glucopyranose residues joined by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A amino disaccharide consisting of N-acetylneuaminic acid and D-galactopyranose joined by a (2->3) glycosidic bond.
An amino disaccharide consisting of a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residue and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-galactopyranosyl residue joined by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A branched amino trisaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 6 have each been glycosylated by a alpha-L-fucopyranosyl group.
A mannopentaose comprising alpha-D-mannopyranose, beta-D-mannopyranose, beta-D-mannopyranose, alpha-D-mannopyranose and D-mannopyranose resideus joined in sequence by (1->2) glycosidic linkages.
